Mukul Sharma was an Indian writer and journalist. He was a former editor of Science Today and was popular for his column Mindsport, that appeared first in The Illustrated Weekly and later in The Sunday Times. His short stories are adapted into Hindi movies A Death in the Gunj, Ek Thi Daayan, 36 Chowringhee Lane and Parama. He also acted in his first wife Aparna Sen's 1984 film Paroma.


